---
title: Bulgogi Beef Tacos with Lime-Ponzu Slaw & Cilantro
description: These fusion-style tacos are packed with ground beef simmered in bulgogi sauce—a Korean-style savory-sweet blend of soy sauce and sesame oil. You’ll load it into warm flour tortillas, top with bright, tangy cabbage-cilantro slaw, and marvel at how seven simple ingredients can come together for a delicious meal in just 15 minutes. Wow!

image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/674e2e41f546e01c8f27741d-a1b3d96a.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/674e2e41f546e01c8f27741d-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/bulgogi-beef-tacos-674e2e41f546e01c8f27741d
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: East Asia
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 790 kcal
  fat: 40 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 65 g
  sugar: 26 g
  protein: 31 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 1610 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
---

Wash and dry produce. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Quarter @lime{1}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, @ponzu sauce{6%ml}, half the cilantro, @sugar{1/8%tsp}, and as much lime juice as you like (be sure to save a squeeze for the next step!). Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Set aside, tossing occasionally, until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}. Carefully drain any excess grease if necessary.

Add @bulgogi sauce{4%ounce} and cook, stirring, until beef is coated and sauce is warmed through, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Turn off heat; stir in a squeeze of lime juice. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{}; microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates; fill with beef, slaw (draining first), and remaining cilantro. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> These fusion-style tacos are packed with ground beef simmered in bulgogi sauce—a Korean-style savory-sweet blend of soy sauce and sesame oil. You'll marvel at how seven simple ingredients can come together for a delicious meal in just 15 minutes. Wow!